# ArgoCD - GitOps Deployment

ArgoCD is installed on the EKS cluster and configured to automatically 
sync Kubernetes manifests from GitHub to the cluster.

## What This Does
- Watches the `deploymentfiles/` folder in this GitHub repository
- Automatically deploys any changes to the EKS cluster
- Provides a visual dashboard showing deployment health and sync status

## ArgoCD Setup
- Installed ArgoCD in its own namespace: `kubectl create namespace argocd`
- Exposed via LoadBalancer service for external access
- Connected to GitHub repository for GitOps sync

## How GitOps Works Here
1. Update deployment.yaml or service.yaml in `deploymentfiles/`
2. Push changes to GitHub
3. ArgoCD detects the change automatically
4. ArgoCD syncs the cluster to match the new state
5. No manual kubectl apply needed

## Application Details
- App Name: tomcat
- Namespace: tomcat
